    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-12-07T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-12-07T04:00:00-05:00" n="235"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d235">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.01/12–749: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Thailand</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stanton</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bangkok</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-12-07T16:00:00+07:00"
                            >December 7, 1949—4 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received December 7—8:32 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1038. Re Saigon’s 422,<note n="67" xml:id="d235fn67">December 5, not
                        printed.</note> might suggest Department once again point out to British
                    hasty recognition Chinese Communist government as apparently contemplated by
                    them will hasten Communist domination Siam and indeed strengthen Communists’
                    influence and increase prestige Commie government throughout SEA.</p>
                <p>Sent Department 1038, repeated Singapore 55, airmailed Saigon.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stanton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
